      {
        "id": "7b150e850f67b8d9d810ac4b7ca755f7a1c234c8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-05 15:07:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Michael, not sure, bit hackish, which could be ok short term, wondering may be better to integrate policy-base/Dockerfile contents in each image, and just get rid of it all together in docker so we don't have to update the Dockerfile with scripts.   What do you guys think?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "964e0939a8155c0852534fda543f3e08fd454b82",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-05 15:21:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nI think we will have to do this, especially once we release and have a branch for Beijing.\nCan you also put this in the verify script? And then \"cat\" the dockerfile just so we can see the exact contents?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "c92016dcd53a603b46460438f23e3f02f20ac86a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-05 15:35:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI meant replace the:\n\n\"FROM ... policy-base\" (first line of Dockerfile) with the actual contents, and discontinue policy-base in the docker repo as a possibility.  I think the Dockerfile from policy-base is minimum.  I question its usefulness.\n\nThere may some other options as setting the docker registry explicitly to nexus ..\n\nWe can submit this, but I think should be revisited in the future, not comfortable with in-flight edits on a Dockerfile.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "38d04978317cdb37e978326b811dcc90ef32ed94",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-05 15:39:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm ok with that approach - then we remove pretty much everything from policy/docker??",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "d09482197112d02e31057b17df7860f685f4fa08",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-05 15:43:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think so with the exception of the docker-compose and associated config files to customize the installation.  That would stay but does not need to be built.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "2be32b974b565827ecd2b47bafc7e374172cd727",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1581,
          "name": "Michael Morris",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michael.morris@ericsson.com",
          "username": "mmis"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-05 15:49:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYes, if you're happy to get rid of the base images then that is definitely a cleaner way. As you said, editing the Dockerfile on the fly is not a great solution",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "8e43b9852d906b190de3a81502d8d95eddf1a240",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-05 15:52:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review\n\nI think we are all in agreement then.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
